<section class="section section--alt" id="trust-standards">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Accountability in practice</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The standards every engagement runs to.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Accountability isn&rsquo;t a promise &mdash; it&rsquo;s an operating model. Every engagement, direct or network, runs to these six standards.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">01</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Free discovery call</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Every engagement begins with a <strong>30-minute discovery call</strong>. Free, no obligation. We surface the right engagement &mdash; or honestly say we&rsquo;re not the right fit.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">02</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Written fixed-fee scope</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>Written scope within 3 business days</strong> of the call. Fixed fee. No hourly billing. If work expands, scope is rewritten and re-approved.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">03</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Certified ProAdvisor delivery</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Delivered by a <strong>Certified Intuit ProAdvisor</strong> &mdash; not a general bookkeeper, not an offshore queue. Credentials verifiable on Intuit&rsquo;s directory.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">04</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Named-operator continuity</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">A <strong>named ProAdvisor owns your account end-to-end</strong>. No account-manager rotation. No re-explaining your business each quarter.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">05</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Direct file access</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">We work <strong>inside your QuickBooks file</strong> as accountant-users. Your books, your data, your audit trail. Never a parallel system, never forced data export.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">06</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">CPA-ready handoff</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Recurring engagements include <strong>year-end CPA handoff at no additional cost</strong>. Tax-prep files and schedules delivered to your CPA on their timeline.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="trust-security">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Data security</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Your data stays yours. Always.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>The single biggest data-security risk in outsourced bookkeeping is the <strong>parallel-system model</strong> &mdash; where a provider exports your financials into their own platform, leaving you without control of your own books. TechBrot doesn&rsquo;t work that way.</p>
      <p>We operate as an <strong>accountant-user inside your existing QuickBooks file</strong>. You grant access; you can revoke it at any time. Your books never leave your control. The QuickBooks audit trail records every action we take and remains visible to you continuously &mdash; you can see exactly what was changed, when, and by whom.</p>
      <p>All working sessions use <strong>encrypted screen-share connections</strong>; file transfers, when needed, use encrypted channels. We follow documented data-handling practices appropriate for sensitive financial information, detailed in our <a href="/legal/dpa/">data processing terms</a> and <a href="/legal/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a>.</p>
      <p>The principle is simple: <strong>you hold the keys.</strong> We&rsquo;re a credentialed professional working in your house, not a vendor who takes your house away to work on it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="trust-scope">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Honest scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What we do, don't do, and coordinate.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Trust includes being honest about limits. Here&rsquo;s the clean read &mdash; stated up front, not buried.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>We do</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Bookkeeping (monthly, cleanup, catch-up). QuickBooks setup, cleanup, migration. Payroll management. Multi-state sales tax compliance. Fractional CFO. CPA-ready year-end handoff. State and local jurisdiction tax operational configuration.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>We don't</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">File federal or state tax returns. Represent clients before the IRS or state agencies. Provide Intuit&rsquo;s software-level technical support. Publish unverified testimonials or inflated performance claims.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>We coordinate with</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Your existing CPA or EA for tax filings. Your tax counsel for audit defense. Sales tax counsel for state-specific tax-position work. We refer to licensed practitioners when scope requires it.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="trust-reviews">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">On reviews</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Why you won't find fake reviews here.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>Most accounting and bookkeeping sites lead with review counts and testimonials. Many are unverified, self-reported, or worse &mdash; fabricated. We&rsquo;ve made a deliberate choice not to play that game.</p>
      <p>TechBrot is building a <strong>verified-review program</strong> with appropriate client consent &mdash; reviews tied to real, documented engagements. Until that program completes, we&rsquo;d rather show you <strong>verifiable facts</strong> than ask you to take unverifiable testimonials on faith:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Active Intuit ProAdvisor certifications</strong> &mdash; checkable on Intuit&rsquo;s public directory.</li>
        <li><strong>Delaware C-Corporation registration</strong> &mdash; TechBrot Inc., founded 2023.</li>
        <li><strong>Transparent fixed-fee pricing</strong> &mdash; published openly on every service page.</li>
        <li><strong>Honest scope</strong> &mdash; what we don&rsquo;t do, stated as clearly as what we do.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>When verified reviews are ready, they&rsquo;ll be published with the same standard of honesty. <strong>A real review program is worth more than a hundred fabricated stars.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

